{
  "name": "WF52 — Content Score Enforcer",
  "nodes": [
    {
      "parameters": {},
      "id": "wf52-manual",
      "name": "Manual Trigger",
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.manualTrigger",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "position": [
        200,
        300
      ]
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "httpMethod": "POST",
        "path": "score-content",
        "responseMode": "responseNode",
        "options": {}
      },
      "id": "wf52-webhook",
      "name": "Webhook Trigger",
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.webhook",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "position": [
        200,
        500
      ],
      "webhookId": "score-content"
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "jsCode": "// Normalize input from webhook or manual trigger\nconst input = $input.first().json;\nconst body = input.body || input;\n\nconst content_id = body.content_id;\nconst file_url = body.file_url || '';\nconst caption = body.caption || '';\nconst business_id = body.business_id;\nconst platform = body.platform || 'instagram';\nconst attempt_number = parseInt(body.attempt_number || '1', 10);\n\nif (!content_id || !business_id) {\n  throw new Error('content_id and business_id are required');\n}\n\nreturn [{ json: { content_id, file_url, caption, business_id, platform, attempt_number } }];"
      },
      "id": "wf52-parse-input",
      "name": "Parse Input",
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.code",
      "typeVersion": 2,
      "position": [
        440,
        400
      ]
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "method": "GET",
        "url": "=https://maroa-api-production.up.railway.app/api/business/{{ $json.business_id }}/brand-dna",
        "options": {}
      },
      "id": "wf52-fetch-brand-dna",
      "name": "Fetch Brand DNA",
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.httpRequest",
      "typeVersion": 4,
      "position": [
        660,
        300
      ],
      "continueOnFail": true
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "method": "GET",
        "url": "=https://serpapi.com/search.json?engine=google&q=best+{{ $('Parse Input').first().json.platform }}+posts+{{ encodeURIComponent($json.industry || 'business') }}+2026&api_key={{ $env.SERPAPI_KEY }}&num=5",
        "options": {}
      },
      "id": "wf52-fetch-trends",
      "name": "Fetch Platform Trends",
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.httpRequest",
      "typeVersion": 4,
      "position": [
        660,
        500
      ],
      "continueOnFail": true
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "jsCode": "const input = $('Parse Input').first().json;\nconst brandDna = $('Fetch Brand DNA').first().json || {};\nconst trendsRaw = $('Fetch Platform Trends').first().json || {};\n\nconst trends = (trendsRaw.organic_results || []).slice(0, 5).map(r => r.snippet || r.title || '').join('\\n');\n\nconst brand = [\n  brandDna.brand_tone ? `Brand tone: ${brandDna.brand_tone}` : '',\n  brandDna.target_audience ? `Target audience: ${brandDna.target_audience}` : '',\n  brandDna.industry ? `Industry: ${brandDna.industry}` : '',\n  brandDna.usp ? `USP: ${brandDna.usp}` : '',\n  brandDna.brand_values ? `Values: ${brandDna.brand_values}` : ''\n].filter(Boolean).join('\\n');\n\nconst scorer_user_text = `You are a professional content quality scorer for social media marketing. You analyze content against 6 dimensions and return a strict score.\n\nBRAND DNA:\n${brand}\n\nCURRENT PLATFORM TRENDS (${input.platform}):\n${trends}\n\nCONTENT TO SCORE:\n- Platform: ${input.platform}\n- Caption: ${input.caption}\n- Image/Video URL: ${input.file_url}\n- Attempt: ${input.attempt_number} of 3\n\nScore each dimension:\n\na. Hook Strength (0-2):\n   Analyze caption first line:\n   - 2: Creates irresistible curiosity or strong emotion\n   - 1: Decent opening but not scroll-stopping\n   - 0: Weak or generic opening\n\nb. Visual Quality (0-2):\n   Analyze the image/video:\n   - 2: Professional, well-lit, perfectly composed\n   - 1: Acceptable quality, minor issues\n   - 0: Poor lighting, composition, or quality\n   If no image URL provided, score based on caption visual language.\n\nc. Brand Alignment (0-1):\n   Compare to brand DNA:\n   - 1: Perfectly matches brand voice and style\n   - 0: Inconsistent with brand identity\n\nd. Trend Relevance (0-2):\n   Compare to current trend data:\n   - 2: Uses current trending format + hashtags\n   - 1: Somewhat relevant to current trends\n   - 0: Outdated or irrelevant format\n\ne. CTA Clarity (0-1):\n   - 1: Clear, compelling call to action\n   - 0: Weak, missing, or confusing CTA\n\nf. Engagement Potential (0-2):\n   - 2: Highly likely to generate comments/shares\n   - 1: Some engagement potential\n   - 0: Unlikely to generate engagement\n\nTotal possible: 10 points.\n\nVerdict rules:\n- total_score >= 7: \"approved\"\n- total_score 5-6 AND attempt_number < 3: \"regenerate\"\n- total_score < 5 OR attempt_number >= 3: \"flag\"\n\nIf verdict is \"regenerate\", provide an improved_prompt that fixes the weaknesses.\nIf verdict is \"flag\", explain why clearly.\n\nReturn only valid JSON:\n{\n  \"total_score\": number,\n  \"breakdown\": { \"hook\": number, \"visual\": number, \"brand\": number, \"trend\": number, \"cta\": number, \"engagement\": number },\n  \"verdict\": \"approved\" | \"regenerate\" | \"flag\",\n  \"improvement_notes\": [\"specific fix 1\", \"specific fix 2\"],\n  \"improved_prompt\": \"string or null\"\n}`;\n\nreturn [{ json: { ...input, brand_context: brand, trend_context: trends, industry: brandDna.industry || 'business', scorer_user_text } }];"
      },
      "id": "wf52-merge-context",
      "name": "Merge Context",
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.code",
      "typeVersion": 2,
      "position": [
        900,
        400
      ]
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "method": "POST",
        "url": "=https://api.anthropic.com/v1/messages",
        "sendHeaders": true,
        "headerParameters": {
          "parameters": [
            {
              "name": "x-api-key",
              "value": "={{ $env.ANTHROPIC_API_KEY }}"
            },
            {
              "name": "anthropic-version",
              "value": "2023-06-01"
            },
            {
              "name": "Content-Type",
              "value": "application/json"
            }
          ]
        },
        "sendBody": true,
        "specifyBody": "json",
        "jsonBody": "={{ JSON.stringify({ model: 'claude-opus-4-5', max_tokens: 2000, messages: [{ role: 'user', content: (($json.file_url || '').trim().startsWith('http')) ? [{ type: 'image', source: { type: 'url', url: $json.file_url } }, { type: 'text', text: $json.scorer_user_text }] : $json.scorer_user_text }] }) }}",
        "options": {
          "timeout": 60000
        }
      },
      "id": "wf52-claude-scorer",
      "name": "Claude Vision Scorer",
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.httpRequest",
      "typeVersion": 4,
      "position": [
        1140,
        400
      ],
      "continueOnFail": true
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "jsCode": "const raw = $input.first().json.content?.[0]?.text || $input.first().json.text || '';\nlet c = {};\ntry { c = JSON.parse(raw); }\ncatch(e) { const m = raw.match(/{[\\s\\S]*}/); if(m) try { c = JSON.parse(m[0]); } catch(e2) {} }\n\nconst input = $('Parse Input').first().json;\nconst total_score = c.total_score || 0;\nconst verdict = c.verdict || (total_score >= 7 ? 'approved' : total_score >= 5 && input.attempt_number < 3 ? 'regenerate' : 'flag');\n\nreturn [{ json: {\n  content_id: input.content_id,\n  business_id: input.business_id,\n  file_url: input.file_url,\n  caption: input.caption,\n  platform: input.platform,\n  attempt_number: input.attempt_number,\n  total_score,\n  breakdown: c.breakdown || {},\n  verdict,\n  improvement_notes: c.improvement_notes || [],\n  improved_prompt: c.improved_prompt || null\n} }];"
      },
      "id": "wf52-parse-score",
      "name": "Parse Score",
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.code",
      "typeVersion": 2,
      "position": [
        1380,
        400
      ]
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "conditions": {
          "string": [
            {
              "value1": "={{ $json.verdict }}",
              "operation": "equals",
              "value2": "approved"
            }
          ]
        }
      },
      "id": "wf52-if-approved",
      "name": "IF Approved",
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.if",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "position": [
        1620,
